fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-001",
  description: "Update kernel-language.md with expression grammar: match/if/let/lambda expression syntax, patterns, operation bodies. Grammar is implemented in tree-sitter and described in Proposal 018, but kernel-language.md (the spec) does not include it.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-001",
  description: "Change let expression syntax from 'let x = value in body' to block-style 'let x = value' (next expression is body). Update grammar.js, converter, and tests. See Proposal 018 let_chain.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-001",
  description: "Add 'end' keyword after operation expression bodies. Needed for block-style let (no 'in' keyword) to delimit where the body ends. Consistent with sort/namespace which also use 'end'. Update grammar.js, converter, and tests.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact Feedback(content: "All deliverables already shipped: predicate-variable parsing (grammar accepts ?variable in fn_term name field), conversion to ho_apply (parse/convert.rs:416-462), pattern-fragment check at load (typing.rs:2367-2488 — head rejection, nested-ho_apply rejection, distinct-args check), resolver dispatch (resolve.rs:491 resolve_ho_apply). Acceptance tests pass: ho_predicate_*, ho_bigint_induction_parses, pattern_fragment_*.", workitem: "WI-104", author: "claude", at: "2026-04-27T10:30:59Z")
fact Feedback(content: "Phase 2 expression typing was already implemented in src/kb/typing.rs prior to claim: check_if_expr, check_let_expr, check_match_expr (with exhaustiveness), check_lambda, check_list_literal, check_set_literal, check_tuple_literal; pattern matching via extend_env_from_pattern (var/constructor/tuple); env extension; fresh type vars via make_type_var. Typing tests cover all forms (type_check_op_if_expr_*, _let_expr_correct, _match_*). All anthill-core tests pass.", workitem: "WI-038", author: "user", at: "2026-05-03T16:43:29Z")
fact Feedback(content: "Resolved via the ?a, ?b form: anthill's logical-variable syntax (already valid as variable_term in type positions) doubles as parametric polymorphism for free-standing operations. No grammar / converter / loader / typer change was required — the resolver opens fresh logical vars per query and the typer instantiates them at each call site. Coverage added: typing_test.rs::wi186_* (5 typing assertions: smoke, return-type, parameterized-return, two concrete call-sites) and tests/wi186_free_standing_parametric_test.rs (4 runtime tests: id at Int / String, two-call-site instantiation, make_pair returning Pair[A=String,B=Int]). Acceptance tool 'cargo-test' green. Note: a future extension to introduce named type parameters (e.g. operation sort[A](x: List[A]) -> List[A] requires Ord[A]) — distinct from ?a — would need a separate proposal extending the type-parameter syntax (analogous to 'sort A = ?' inside sort bodies); not required by WI-186 itself.", workitem: "WI-186", author: "user", at: "2026-05-06T17:20:42Z")
fact Feedback(content: "DELIVERED. Root cause: each type-parameter was represented by TWO distinct Var(Global)s — one allocated by type_expr_to_term's fallback path (when the entity field referenced the param before its SortAlias registered), one by load_abstract_sort's convert_term(?) on the anonymous '?'. Pattern substitution then bound one Var while walk_type visited the other. Loader fix in kb/load.rs: (a) load_sort_with_body pre-loads nested AbstractSort declarations before the FieldInfo loop, so SortAlias is in place when type_expr_to_term first runs on field types; (b) load_abstract_sort dedupes on already-asserted SortAlias so the later load_items pass safely no-ops; (c) find_sort_alias_var two-pass (exact-Symbol first, short-name fallback) so qualified lookups beat short-name collisions. Typer fix in kb/typing.rs: build_pattern_subst takes parent_sort: Symbol; check_value_against_parameterized switched from unscoped resolve_sort_alias(short) to type_param_vid_in_sort(parent, param) — parent-scoped via try_resolve_symbol of the qualified name + exact-match resolve_sort_alias. Tests: scripts/test.sh -p anthill-core 831/831; bundle anthill-todo --anthill list exits 0 with clean stderr. New regression tests: typing_test::wi237_pattern_subst_concrete_field_type, wi237_pattern_subst_parameterized_field_type pin propagation for bare-Var and parameterized field types. Unblocks WI-204 Phase A.", at: "2026-05-17T08:53:06Z", workitem: "WI-237", author: "user")
